  "text": "While extensive literature on the benefits of speed planning for CAVs and usage of multi-speed transmissions for BEVs exist, little research has been reported addressing the combination of these two technologies. In [CITATION_1] , optimizations at the vehicle level and at the powertrain level are performed concurrently for application to cruise control, in which the vehicle is controlled to track a constant reference speed and real-time traffic information is not exploited. Co-optimization of vehicle speed and powertrain control according to signal timing of traffic lights is presented in [CITATION_2] .",
